# TypeScript Rules
- no-any: Avoid using the 'any' type - it defeats TypeScript's type safety
- strict-null-checks: Always enable strict null checks for better type safety
- explicit-return-type: Use explicit return types on functions
- no-unused-vars: Remove unused variables and imports

# Python Rules
- type-hints: Always use type hints for function parameters and return values
- f-strings: Use f-strings instead of older string formatting methods
- docstrings: Include docstrings for all functions and classes
- line-length: Keep lines under 88 characters

# JavaScript Rules
- prefer-const: Use const for variables that aren't reassigned
- no-var: Never use var, prefer let or const
- template-literals: Use template literals instead of string concatenation
- arrow-functions: Use arrow functions for callbacks